00:01:53.613 --> 00:01:56.324 position:50% align:center
Polling shows we've got
almost 90% of the vote.

00:01:56.408 --> 00:01:58.368 position:50% align:center
You're worrying over nothing.

00:01:58.451 --> 00:02:00.036 position:50% align:center
I think we've got
this election on lock.

00:02:00.120 --> 00:02:01.788 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] Unless they have
something up their sleeve

00:02:01.871 --> 00:02:02.914 position:50% align:center
we're unaware of.

00:02:02.997 --> 00:02:05.083 position:50% align:center
Nope. Nada.

00:02:05.166 --> 00:02:08.503 position:50% align:center
We're definitely gonna win
today's election, no doubt.

00:02:08.586 --> 00:02:09.963 position:50% align:center
Why just win, though?

00:02:10.046 --> 00:02:12.924 position:50% align:center
We should make it an
indisputable shutout.

00:02:13.008 --> 00:02:16.428 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Is there something
between you and Miko Iino?

00:02:22.142 --> 00:02:24.144 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
What are you doing, Miko?

00:02:24.227 --> 00:02:25.979 position:50% align:center
Making the sign for
a person on your palm

00:02:26.062 --> 00:02:28.690 position:50% align:center
and swallowing it
calms the nerves.

00:02:28.773 --> 00:02:30.400 position:50% align:center
Would you care to try?

00:02:30.483 --> 00:02:32.444 position:50% align:center
Interesting.

00:02:35.530 --> 00:02:36.573 position:50% align:center
Can't do it.

00:02:36.656 --> 00:02:38.033 position:50% align:center
What? Why?

00:02:38.116 --> 00:02:41.202 position:50% align:center
I'm entirely too empathetic
to swallow another person.

00:02:41.286 --> 00:02:42.996 position:50% align:center
It makes me feel guilty.

00:02:43.079 --> 00:02:44.581 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
What're you talking about?

00:02:44.664 --> 00:02:46.666 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] What if he has a
loving family waiting for him

00:02:46.750 --> 00:02:47.667 position:50% align:center
to come home?

00:02:47.751 --> 00:02:48.668 position:50% align:center
He doesn't.

00:02:48.752 --> 00:02:49.961 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
Then he's all alone.

00:02:50.045 --> 00:02:51.254 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
You're missing the point.

00:02:51.338 --> 00:02:54.049 position:50% align:center
He needs a name,
and that name is Yusaku.

00:02:54.132 --> 00:02:56.801 position:50% align:center
Naming him makes it even
tougher to swallow him.

00:02:56.885 --> 00:02:58.345 position:50% align:center
Hey, we're about
to start, you two.

00:02:58.428 --> 00:03:00.722 position:50% align:center
Oh, thanks!

00:03:02.140 --> 00:03:03.266 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:03:08.438 --> 00:03:10.732 position:50% align:center
Go. You've got this.

00:03:12.233 --> 00:03:14.069 position:50% align:center
Uh! You ate Yusaku!

00:03:14.986 --> 00:03:18.656 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS murmuring]

00:03:18.740 --> 00:03:22.660 position:50% align:center
Miko Iino is an incredibly
honest individual!

00:03:22.744 --> 00:03:25.246 position:50% align:center
She's one of the
purest girls I know.

00:03:25.330 --> 00:03:29.000 position:50% align:center
Someone who lives her life
with purpose and great intent.

00:03:29.084 --> 00:03:30.627 position:50% align:center
Most of you are well aware.

00:03:30.710 --> 00:03:32.712 position:50% align:center
You've seen her work through
the Public Morals Committee

00:03:32.796 --> 00:03:34.714 position:50% align:center
and you know how earnest she is.

00:03:34.798 --> 00:03:36.841 position:50% align:center
She's been part of that
committee since middle school,

00:03:36.925 --> 00:03:39.803 position:50% align:center
demonstrating her loyalty to
the academy for several years.

00:03:39.886 --> 00:03:41.054 position:50% align:center
And she's as devoted
to her studies...

00:03:41.137 --> 00:03:42.889 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
No hesitation.

00:03:42.972 --> 00:03:45.141 position:50% align:center
She must've practiced a lot.

00:03:45.225 --> 00:03:49.062 position:50% align:center
Perhaps, but nobody's
really paying attention.

00:03:49.145 --> 00:03:52.065 position:50% align:center
Half of the students are
in their own little worlds.

00:03:52.148 --> 00:03:53.566 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] So when it
comes time to vote,

00:03:53.650 --> 00:03:57.153 position:50% align:center
please vote for Miko Iino!

00:03:57.237 --> 00:04:00.699 position:50% align:center
Thank you. This
concludes my speech.

00:04:00.782 --> 00:04:01.574 position:50% align:center
[STAFF 6A]
Well done.

00:04:01.658 --> 00:04:03.535 position:50% align:center
Now, on behalf of Mr. Shirogane,

00:04:03.618 --> 00:04:05.328 position:50% align:center
Miss Shinomiya will
give a few words.

00:04:05.412 --> 00:04:06.871 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS murmuring]

00:04:06.955 --> 00:04:07.914 position:50% align:center
Yay, Kaguya.

00:04:07.997 --> 00:04:09.249 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 6C]
She's honor incarnate!

00:04:17.549 --> 00:04:18.842 position:50% align:center
[microphone hums]

00:04:18.925 --> 00:04:19.718 position:50% align:center
[gasps]

00:04:19.801 --> 00:04:23.054 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS gasping, chattering]

00:04:25.974 --> 00:04:28.643 position:50% align:center
My name is Kaguya Shinomiya,
and I'm here in support

00:04:28.727 --> 00:04:31.396 position:50% align:center
of presidential candidate
Miyuki Shirogane.

00:04:31.479 --> 00:04:33.523 position:50% align:center
Let us begin. As you all know...

00:04:33.606 --> 00:04:35.692 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] That mic
feedback was deliberate.

00:04:35.775 --> 00:04:38.653 position:50% align:center
She wanted to make sure she had
everyone's undivided attention,

00:04:38.737 --> 00:04:40.530 position:50% align:center
teachers included.

00:04:40.613 --> 00:04:41.823 position:50% align:center
[TEACHER 6A grunts]

00:04:41.906 --> 00:04:43.241 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
Hm?

00:04:44.242 --> 00:04:46.036 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] For starters,
the council can't do anything

00:04:46.119 --> 00:04:47.954 position:50% align:center
without monetary contributions.

00:04:48.038 --> 00:04:49.414 position:50% align:center
Needless to say,

00:04:49.497 --> 00:04:52.917 position:50% align:center
we have to be smart and ensure
that money isn't wasted.

00:04:53.001 --> 00:04:56.212 position:50% align:center
And we do that by having an
effective management of assets.

00:04:56.296 --> 00:04:58.006 position:50% align:center
As the graph you see
here indicates,

00:04:58.089 --> 00:05:00.050 position:50% align:center
the year we were most successful
in how we made use

00:05:00.133 --> 00:05:02.260 position:50% align:center
of our finances and resources
was the year we had

00:05:02.344 --> 00:05:04.304 position:50% align:center
former President
Shirogane's leadership...

00:05:04.387 --> 00:05:05.597 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
Yeah, come to think of it,

00:05:05.680 --> 00:05:07.057 position:50% align:center
they do get the job done.

00:05:07.140 --> 00:05:09.059 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 6R]
So what?

00:05:09.142 --> 00:05:10.810 position:50% align:center
That still doesn't
make him a pureblood.

00:05:10.894 --> 00:05:13.188 position:50% align:center
Stop. You should be
paying attention.

00:05:13.271 --> 00:05:14.773 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] President Shirogane
always considered...

00:05:14.856 --> 00:05:17.692 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] Fujiwara knew that
was an anti-Shirogane section

00:05:17.776 --> 00:05:20.153 position:50% align:center
and escorted a teacher
to stand by them.

00:05:20.236 --> 00:05:22.655 position:50% align:center
They know exactly
what they're doing.

00:05:22.739 --> 00:05:24.240 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Finally, to help explain

00:05:24.324 --> 00:05:28.411 position:50% align:center
our forthcoming club policies,
I've prepared a video.

00:05:28.495 --> 00:05:31.289 position:50% align:center
We're going to let a student
survey decide the destination

00:05:31.373 --> 00:05:32.707 position:50% align:center
of the class trip this year.

00:05:32.791 --> 00:05:36.878 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS gasping, chattering]

00:05:36.961 --> 00:05:40.840 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] This way, everybody
can have a say in the matter.

00:05:40.924 --> 00:05:44.511 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS chattering]

00:05:44.594 --> 00:05:46.846 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] Shirogane cares,
and to demonstrate that,

00:05:46.930 --> 00:05:49.182 position:50% align:center
he brought back one our
favorite teachers of all time

00:05:49.265 --> 00:05:51.434 position:50% align:center
to lead a special class.

00:05:51.518 --> 00:05:55.480 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] The only thing this
video promotes is propaganda.

00:05:55.563 --> 00:05:57.357 position:50% align:center
Ishigami.

00:05:58.358 --> 00:05:59.984 position:50% align:center
They're really eating it up.

00:06:00.068 --> 00:06:02.278 position:50% align:center
It's an approximation of
the things you've accomplished

00:06:02.362 --> 00:06:04.739 position:50% align:center
and what people can expect.

00:06:04.823 --> 00:06:07.784 position:50% align:center
What matters is how those
things are presented.

00:06:07.867 --> 00:06:10.745 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] Still, I think you put
a little more effort into it

00:06:10.829 --> 00:06:12.247 position:50% align:center
than you needed to.

00:06:12.330 --> 00:06:14.290 position:50% align:center
[YU]
Remember what I told you?

00:06:14.374 --> 00:06:17.293 position:50% align:center
I wanna beat Miko Iino
in a landslide.

00:06:17.377 --> 00:06:18.461 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Thank you.

00:06:18.545 --> 00:06:21.006 position:50% align:center
I appreciate your time
and consideration.

00:06:22.173 --> 00:06:24.467 position:50% align:center
Vote for Miyuki
Shirogane's second term.

00:06:24.551 --> 00:06:27.804 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS cheering]

00:06:27.887 --> 00:06:29.222 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
Impressive.

00:06:29.305 --> 00:06:32.684 position:50% align:center
Both her speech and
unshakeable resolve.

00:06:32.767 --> 00:06:36.271 position:50% align:center
Miko has just as many
accomplishments. But...

00:06:36.354 --> 00:06:37.272 position:50% align:center
[STAFF 6A]
Next, we'll hear from

00:06:37.355 --> 00:06:40.108 position:50% align:center
presidential candidate
Miko Iino.

00:06:42.610 --> 00:06:43.695 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
Hmph.

00:06:52.162 --> 00:06:54.247 position:50% align:center
My name is... Miko Iino.

00:06:54.330 --> 00:06:55.123 position:50% align:center
I can't hear her.

00:06:55.206 --> 00:06:55.832 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 6E]
Did she start?

00:06:55.915 --> 00:06:56.875 position:50% align:center
What'd she say?

00:06:56.958 --> 00:06:58.293 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 6T]
We can't hear you!

00:06:58.376 --> 00:06:59.669 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 6G]
Yeah! Speak up!

00:06:59.753 --> 00:07:03.423 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
I'm, uh... Miko Iino.

00:07:03.506 --> 00:07:04.924 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 6H laughs]

00:07:05.008 --> 00:07:06.801 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 6I]
Don't tell me she's nervous.

00:07:06.885 --> 00:07:12.891 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS chattering, laughing]

00:07:16.227 --> 00:07:18.188 position:50% align:center
[YU]
Yep. Same pattern.

00:07:18.271 --> 00:07:21.066 position:50% align:center
This is why she's
never won an election.

00:07:21.149 --> 00:07:23.777 position:50% align:center
She's always been garbage
in front of a crowd,

00:07:23.860 --> 00:07:26.654 position:50% align:center
and every time she
loses, it gets worse.

00:07:28.448 --> 00:07:31.242 position:50% align:center
It's laughable.

00:07:31.326 --> 00:07:36.081 position:50% align:center
She's a model student.
Strait-laced, top-of-the-class.

00:07:36.164 --> 00:07:37.374 position:50% align:center
And she also happens to be

00:07:37.457 --> 00:07:40.835 position:50% align:center
a self-important, authoritarian
pain in the ass.

00:07:40.919 --> 00:07:42.921 position:50% align:center
So exposing herself
to ridicule like this

00:07:43.004 --> 00:07:44.714 position:50% align:center
is a bold move on her part.

00:07:44.798 --> 00:07:46.925 position:50% align:center
She annoys tons of
people on the daily.

00:07:47.008 --> 00:07:51.429 position:50% align:center
They might even feel
justified laughing at her.

00:07:51.513 --> 00:07:54.724 position:50% align:center
I get it because I have
reasons to resent her, too.

00:07:57.227 --> 00:08:02.482 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS laughing]

00:08:02.565 --> 00:08:04.901 position:50% align:center
But still, it pisses me off.

00:08:04.984 --> 00:08:08.363 position:50% align:center
She shouldn't get laughed
at for caring so much.

00:08:08.446 --> 00:08:09.906 position:50% align:center
That isn't right.

00:08:09.989 --> 00:08:11.700 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Leave it to me.

00:08:13.118 --> 00:08:16.996 position:50% align:center
We'll beat her, but in a way
that's honorable and fair.

00:08:17.080 --> 00:08:18.623 position:50% align:center
[YU gasps]

00:08:26.840 --> 00:08:29.050 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
Are your parents here, Miko?

00:08:29.134 --> 00:08:33.388 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] No. Mama is busy
distributing vaccines.

00:08:33.471 --> 00:08:36.391 position:50% align:center
And Papa has to work late
hours at the courthouse.

00:08:36.474 --> 00:08:39.644 position:50% align:center
They both have
very important jobs.

00:08:39.728 --> 00:08:42.897 position:50% align:center
But don't you get kind of lonely
if you're at home all alone?

00:08:42.981 --> 00:08:45.066 position:50% align:center
Yes.

00:08:45.150 --> 00:08:48.778 position:50% align:center
You handle it much
better than I would.

00:08:48.862 --> 00:08:51.656 position:50% align:center
It's not their fault, you know?

00:08:51.740 --> 00:08:53.450 position:50% align:center
The world is full of bad people,

00:08:53.533 --> 00:08:55.827 position:50% align:center
and the more there are,
the less I see my parents

00:08:55.910 --> 00:08:58.830 position:50% align:center
because they have
to deal with them.

00:08:58.913 --> 00:09:00.081 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI gasps]

00:09:00.165 --> 00:09:03.293 position:50% align:center
I wish everyone would
just follow the rules!

00:09:03.376 --> 00:09:06.171 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
Miko is a very serious person.

00:09:06.254 --> 00:09:09.007 position:50% align:center
In elementary school, she'd get
to class early every morning

00:09:09.090 --> 00:09:13.303 position:50% align:center
just so she could feed the
fish and water the flowers.

00:09:13.386 --> 00:09:15.263 position:50% align:center
She always had the
highest grade in class,

00:09:15.347 --> 00:09:16.806 position:50% align:center
no matter what the subject,

00:09:16.890 --> 00:09:19.601 position:50% align:center
and did whatever the teacher
said without question.

00:09:19.684 --> 00:09:20.894 position:50% align:center
Listen up!

00:09:20.977 --> 00:09:22.312 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] It only made sense
that she would run

00:09:22.395 --> 00:09:24.898 position:50% align:center
for Student Council President.

00:09:24.981 --> 00:09:26.733 position:50% align:center
I implore you,
stop bringing items

00:09:26.816 --> 00:09:29.569 position:50% align:center
that impede your
education to school!

00:09:29.652 --> 00:09:32.989 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
Miko loves doing what's right.

00:09:33.073 --> 00:09:35.825 position:50% align:center
But most elementary kids
just wanna have fun.

00:09:35.909 --> 00:09:37.410 position:50% align:center
And, of course,
the right thing to do

00:09:37.494 --> 00:09:40.538 position:50% align:center
isn't always the
fun thing to do.

00:09:40.622 --> 00:09:45.085 position:50% align:center
In middle school, we joined
the Public Morals Committee.

00:09:45.168 --> 00:09:47.796 position:50% align:center
Miko didn't hesitate to crack
down on upperclassmen.

00:09:47.879 --> 00:09:51.091 position:50% align:center
It didn't matter how popular
or scary they were.

00:09:51.174 --> 00:09:54.219 position:50% align:center
And a lot of students
didn't appreciate that.

00:09:56.179 --> 00:09:59.015 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] Some even
acted out maliciously,

00:09:59.099 --> 00:10:00.850 position:50% align:center
but Miko didn't care.

00:10:00.934 --> 00:10:03.353 position:50% align:center
She'd brush it off
like it was nothing,

00:10:03.436 --> 00:10:06.189 position:50% align:center
or at least, that's
what people thought.

00:10:06.272 --> 00:10:08.108 position:50% align:center
But they were wrong.

00:10:08.191 --> 00:10:11.528 position:50% align:center
Miko would cry when
nobody else could see.

00:10:11.611 --> 00:10:14.948 position:50% align:center
She was hurt by the mean things
that were said and done to her.

00:10:15.031 --> 00:10:17.200 position:50% align:center
Just like anyone would be.

00:10:17.283 --> 00:10:18.910 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
Miko?

00:10:19.953 --> 00:10:21.496 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
She may be serious,

00:10:21.579 --> 00:10:23.873 position:50% align:center
but that doesn't always
equal strong.

00:10:23.957 --> 00:10:27.544 position:50% align:center
No one seems understand that.

00:10:27.627 --> 00:10:30.463 position:50% align:center
Miko cares about one
thing and one thing only.

00:10:30.547 --> 00:10:32.507 position:50% align:center
Doing what's right.

00:10:34.300 --> 00:10:36.886 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] Why do they have to
look at her like she's a freak?

00:10:36.970 --> 00:10:38.888 position:50% align:center
I'd be scared, too.

00:10:40.432 --> 00:10:41.850 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:10:50.316 --> 00:10:53.403 position:50% align:center
Okay. I think that's enough.

00:10:55.280 --> 00:10:56.448 position:50% align:center
Please, no.

00:10:56.531 --> 00:10:58.700 position:50% align:center
With ridiculous
promises like this,

00:10:58.783 --> 00:11:00.994 position:50% align:center
do you honestly think
you'll get any votes?

00:11:01.077 --> 00:11:02.579 position:50% align:center
I don't.

00:11:02.662 --> 00:11:04.789 position:50% align:center
I, uh... yeah.

00:11:04.873 --> 00:11:06.583 position:50% align:center
You've gotta be kidding me.

00:11:06.666 --> 00:11:09.210 position:50% align:center
Mandatory shaved heads
in this day and age?

00:11:09.294 --> 00:11:10.378 position:50% align:center
Nobody would go for that.

00:11:10.462 --> 00:11:11.421 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:11:11.504 --> 00:11:13.340 position:50% align:center
But there are
plenty of benefits!

00:11:13.423 --> 00:11:14.507 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gasps]

00:11:16.593 --> 00:11:17.510 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
If you believe that,

00:11:17.594 --> 00:11:19.637 position:50% align:center
