You're wrong.

00:11:42.744 --> 00:11:45.246 position:50% align:center
My campaign promises
aren't ridiculous at all!

00:11:45.330 --> 00:11:49.000 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS gasping, chattering]

00:11:49.084 --> 00:11:51.086 position:50% align:center
Are you listening?

00:11:51.169 --> 00:11:53.004 position:50% align:center
Behind me is a survey
of the brand images

00:11:53.088 --> 00:11:54.547 position:50% align:center
of well-known high schools!

00:11:54.631 --> 00:11:56.883 position:50% align:center
You'll notice our academy's
reputation has been declining

00:11:56.966 --> 00:11:59.094 position:50% align:center
with each passing year!

00:11:59.177 --> 00:12:01.763 position:50% align:center
Oh. And you've
identified the cause?

00:12:01.846 --> 00:12:03.390 position:50% align:center
There are numerous reasons,

00:12:03.473 --> 00:12:05.016 position:50% align:center
but the most alarming
one is the impression

00:12:05.100 --> 00:12:06.685 position:50% align:center
our morals aren't up to snuff!

00:12:06.768 --> 00:12:08.019 position:50% align:center
The general public sees us

00:12:08.103 --> 00:12:09.688 position:50% align:center
as "spoiled brats
with good grades."

00:12:09.771 --> 00:12:11.731 position:50% align:center
Is that how you wanna be viewed?

00:12:11.815 --> 00:12:13.108 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS murmuring]

00:12:13.191 --> 00:12:14.776 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI] She's actually
saying what she wanted

00:12:14.859 --> 00:12:16.319 position:50% align:center
to tell everyone!

00:12:16.403 --> 00:12:19.698 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] ...from any community
organizations for our events!

00:12:19.781 --> 00:12:20.657 position:50% align:center
And which community
organizations...?

00:12:20.740 --> 00:12:22.200 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
It's because of him.

00:12:22.283 --> 00:12:25.787 position:50% align:center
Thanks to Shirogane, she's not
worried about the audience.

00:12:25.870 --> 00:12:28.665 position:50% align:center
The neighborhood association
certainly recalls that night.

00:12:28.748 --> 00:12:30.291 position:50% align:center
That's why they stopped
granting us permission

00:12:30.375 --> 00:12:32.335 position:50% align:center
for nighttime activities.

00:12:32.419 --> 00:12:35.463 position:50% align:center
That would've never happened
if our morals weren't so lax!

00:12:35.547 --> 00:12:38.425 position:50% align:center
Our reputation would be better
if regulations were stricter.

00:12:38.508 --> 00:12:41.219 position:50% align:center
Because rules give rise
to good behavior!

00:12:41.302 --> 00:12:43.013 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] But making the
boys shave their heads

00:12:43.096 --> 00:12:44.973 position:50% align:center
is going a little too far.

00:12:45.056 --> 00:12:47.684 position:50% align:center
Any guy with a shaved
head looks hot!

00:12:47.767 --> 00:12:49.519 position:50% align:center
It's both stylish and uniform!

00:12:49.602 --> 00:12:51.730 position:50% align:center
Plus, big round heads
give me palpitations!

00:12:51.813 --> 00:12:53.398 position:50% align:center
So it's fetish of yours?!

00:12:53.481 --> 00:12:55.734 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] We live in the age of
information where you never know

00:12:55.817 --> 00:12:57.986 position:50% align:center
what trivial problem
will ruin a brand.

00:12:58.069 --> 00:13:00.196 position:50% align:center
Our academy is one of the
top schools in the country

00:13:00.280 --> 00:13:03.283 position:50% align:center
and I'd like to keep it that
way even after I graduate!

00:13:03.366 --> 00:13:05.994 position:50% align:center
In conclusion, we need
to start by reforming

00:13:06.077 --> 00:13:08.788 position:50% align:center
the school's image into
a more moral Shuchiin!

00:13:08.872 --> 00:13:14.336 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS chattering]

00:13:14.419 --> 00:13:16.504 position:50% align:center
Is there proof shaved heads
would make a difference?

00:13:16.588 --> 00:13:19.007 position:50% align:center
[MIKO] Yes, it's been proven
to decrease tardiness.

00:13:19.090 --> 00:13:20.091 position:50% align:center
When boys don't waste time

00:13:20.175 --> 00:13:21.176 position:50% align:center
fixing their hair
in the morning,

00:13:21.259 --> 00:13:23.303 position:50% align:center
they get to school much earlier.

00:13:23.386 --> 00:13:24.888 position:50% align:center
It's gonna take a
lot more than that

00:13:24.971 --> 00:13:26.389 position:50% align:center
to make it valid in my book,

00:13:26.473 --> 00:13:29.642 position:50% align:center
especially since modern society
encourages diversity.

00:13:29.726 --> 00:13:31.102 position:50% align:center
Moot point!

00:13:31.186 --> 00:13:33.271 position:50% align:center
While haircuts <i>can</i> be
an expression of self,

00:13:33.355 --> 00:13:35.440 position:50% align:center
there are other ways
to be diverse!

00:13:35.523 --> 00:13:37.942 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] We'd still be deprived
of one of those ways.

00:13:38.026 --> 00:13:39.235 position:50% align:center
That fact remains.

00:13:39.319 --> 00:13:40.987 position:50% align:center
What we need is to
strike a balance

00:13:41.071 --> 00:13:43.990 position:50% align:center
between the ideal of the school
and the unique student.

00:13:44.074 --> 00:13:45.909 position:50% align:center
That's exactly what
clubs are for!

00:13:45.992 --> 00:13:47.077 position:50% align:center
They're an outlet for students

00:13:47.160 --> 00:13:49.120 position:50% align:center
to cultivate their
individuality!

00:13:49.204 --> 00:13:51.831 position:50% align:center
This is one ideal
we can realize!

00:13:51.915 --> 00:13:53.249 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
Their debate went back and forth

00:13:53.333 --> 00:13:55.335 position:50% align:center
for more than half an hour,

00:13:55.418 --> 00:13:58.296 position:50% align:center
but nobody stepped in
to try and stop them.

00:14:01.424 --> 00:14:02.550 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
Unfortunately,

00:14:02.634 --> 00:14:04.928 position:50% align:center
she ended up losing
the election after all.

00:14:05.011 --> 00:14:06.388 position:50% align:center
[MIKO gaspds]

00:14:07.430 --> 00:14:08.723 position:50% align:center
[MIKO sighs]

00:14:08.807 --> 00:14:10.517 position:50% align:center
It's okay.

00:14:10.600 --> 00:14:12.185 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 6V]
Yo, Iino.

00:14:13.228 --> 00:14:18.274 position:50% align:center
[STUDENTS chuckling]

00:14:18.358 --> 00:14:19.526 position:50% align:center
What a close call!

00:14:19.609 --> 00:14:21.528 position:50% align:center
I voted for you,
but he still won!

00:14:21.611 --> 00:14:22.946 position:50% align:center
The poised way you
held your ground

00:14:23.029 --> 00:14:24.155 position:50% align:center
against him was super cool!

00:14:24.239 --> 00:14:25.824 position:50% align:center
Your words were so motivational!

00:14:25.907 --> 00:14:27.075 position:50% align:center
I'm inspired.

00:14:27.158 --> 00:14:29.119 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 6W]
Please tell me you'll run again.

00:14:29.202 --> 00:14:30.537 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 6X]
I didn't see it before,

00:14:30.620 --> 00:14:33.289 position:50% align:center
but you think about the academy
quite a bit, don't you?

00:14:40.463 --> 00:14:42.382 position:50% align:center
[STUDENT 6Y] Man, if Shirogane
wasn't your opponent,

00:14:42.465 --> 00:14:43.633 position:50% align:center
you would've won.

00:14:43.717 --> 00:14:44.676 position:50% align:center
You think?

00:14:44.759 --> 00:14:46.094 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
Miko!

00:14:46.177 --> 00:14:49.222 position:50% align:center
I'm so happy for you,
I think I might start crying!

00:14:49.305 --> 00:14:52.308 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
You're kind of already crying.

00:14:54.602 --> 00:14:55.937 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
Sheesh!

00:14:56.021 --> 00:14:58.273 position:50% align:center
Your recklessness nearly
gave me a heart attack.

00:14:58.356 --> 00:14:59.983 position:50% align:center
So don't make it a habit.

00:15:00.066 --> 00:15:01.860 position:50% align:center
What happened to Shinomiya?

00:15:01.943 --> 00:15:04.237 position:50% align:center
Her stomach hurts so bad,
she can't stand up.

00:15:04.320 --> 00:15:06.156 position:50% align:center
Thanks to someone I know.

00:15:06.239 --> 00:15:08.742 position:50% align:center
Easy with the death glare. Uh.

00:15:10.952 --> 00:15:12.454 position:50% align:center
That's right.

00:15:12.537 --> 00:15:15.123 position:50% align:center
We're gonna need someone to be
in charge of general affairs.

00:15:15.206 --> 00:15:17.208 position:50% align:center
Yeah, I guess so. Uh.

00:15:17.292 --> 00:15:20.378 position:50% align:center
Wait, what do you mean by that?

00:15:20.462 --> 00:15:23.131 position:50% align:center
I hear the wheels
in your head turning.

00:15:24.841 --> 00:15:26.843 position:50% align:center
[NARRATOR]
280 to 320.

00:15:26.926 --> 00:15:29.346 position:50% align:center
Not quite the landslide
he was hoping for.

00:15:29.429 --> 00:15:31.056 position:50% align:center
Cuttin' it kinda close,
huh, Shirogane?

00:15:31.139 --> 00:15:32.098 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Too close!

00:15:32.182 --> 00:15:34.017 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
He did it!

00:15:34.100 --> 00:15:37.228 position:50% align:center
How cool is that?
He's the president again!

00:15:37.312 --> 00:15:41.066 position:50% align:center
When he stepped on that stage,
a small part of me died inside.

00:15:41.149 --> 00:15:43.943 position:50% align:center
I wasn't worried. Debates are
part of politics, that's all.

00:15:44.027 --> 00:15:46.988 position:50% align:center
Uh. But of course
<i>you</i> knew he'd win!

00:15:47.072 --> 00:15:49.616 position:50% align:center
It wouldn't hurt to crack
a smile about it, though!

00:15:52.243 --> 00:15:54.329 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
Lady Kaguya?

00:15:54.412 --> 00:15:55.705 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA gasps]

00:15:58.750 --> 00:16:00.919 position:50% align:center
It's over. You're all right.

00:16:01.002 --> 00:16:03.380 position:50% align:center
I'm sure you must've
been really nervous.

00:16:03.463 --> 00:16:05.423 position:50% align:center
But it's all okay now.

00:16:05.507 --> 00:16:07.384 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA]
That's not it.

00:16:07.467 --> 00:16:09.135 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA]
Maybe you're just tired.

00:16:09.219 --> 00:16:12.806 position:50% align:center
I know you haven't been sleeping
well these past few nights.

00:16:12.889 --> 00:16:15.392 position:50% align:center
And you've been working so hard.

00:16:15.475 --> 00:16:17.686 position:50% align:center
--You can lean on me for...
--[CHIKA] Kaguya!

00:16:19.229 --> 00:16:21.064 position:50% align:center
Are you okay? What happened?

00:16:21.147 --> 00:16:25.568 position:50% align:center
Is it your stomach again?
Darn you, Miyuki!

00:16:26.861 --> 00:16:29.280 position:50% align:center
I hope you won't hold
a grudge against me.

00:16:29.364 --> 00:16:31.032 position:50% align:center
I tried to fight fair.

00:16:31.116 --> 00:16:32.784 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Are you kidding me?

00:16:32.867 --> 00:16:34.160 position:50% align:center
If you hadn't stepped
in when you did,

00:16:34.244 --> 00:16:36.204 position:50% align:center
I would've stayed frozen
behind that podium

00:16:36.287 --> 00:16:38.623 position:50% align:center
and nobody would've
heard about my ideals.

00:16:38.707 --> 00:16:41.001 position:50% align:center
I don't think I can
thank you enough.

00:16:41.084 --> 00:16:42.210 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Uh-huh.

00:16:42.293 --> 00:16:46.923 position:50% align:center
You say that... but your
face says otherwise.

00:16:47.007 --> 00:16:50.593 position:50% align:center
It's a complex mix of
gratefulness and frustration.

00:16:50.677 --> 00:16:52.762 position:50% align:center
Well, all that aside,

00:16:52.846 --> 00:16:55.932 position:50% align:center
would you two be interested
in joining Student Council?

00:16:57.892 --> 00:16:59.728 position:50% align:center
If you're thinking of
running again in the future,

00:16:59.811 --> 00:17:01.855 position:50% align:center
it'd be good to get some
practical experience

00:17:01.938 --> 00:17:02.814 position:50% align:center
under your belt.

00:17:02.897 --> 00:17:03.565 position:50% align:center
What do you say?

00:17:03.648 --> 00:17:04.649 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
No thanks.

00:17:04.733 --> 00:17:06.526 position:50% align:center
If I'm being honest here,

00:17:06.609 --> 00:17:08.778 position:50% align:center
Student Council holds
no interest for me.

00:17:08.862 --> 00:17:10.447 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Huh? Really?

00:17:10.530 --> 00:17:11.364 position:50% align:center
[OSARAGI]
I was only doing this

00:17:11.448 --> 00:17:13.742 position:50% align:center
because I wanted
to support Miko.

00:17:13.825 --> 00:17:15.076 position:50% align:center
Of course.

00:17:15.160 --> 00:17:17.996 position:50% align:center
I completely understand
where you're coming from.

00:17:18.079 --> 00:17:19.497 position:50% align:center
How about you?

00:17:19.581 --> 00:17:21.541 position:50% align:center
I... don't know.

00:17:21.624 --> 00:17:25.211 position:50% align:center
This is the first time I've been
invited to join a council.

00:17:27.339 --> 00:17:30.258 position:50% align:center
Please give me a little
time to think about it.

00:17:30.342 --> 00:17:31.468 position:50% align:center
Fair enough.

00:17:31.551 --> 00:17:33.136 position:50% align:center
Come to the Student
Council office tomorrow

00:17:33.219 --> 00:17:34.304 position:50% align:center
if you choose to join.

00:17:34.387 --> 00:17:35.555 position:50% align:center
Sound good?

00:17:35.638 --> 00:17:37.140 position:50% align:center
[MIKO]
Mh-hm.

00:17:40.060 --> 00:17:41.227 position:50% align:center
One last thing.

00:17:41.311 --> 00:17:43.730 position:50% align:center
You've got some fidgety
creepers behind you.

00:17:43.813 --> 00:17:46.524 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI]
Hm? Uh... Something wrong?

00:17:46.608 --> 00:17:49.069 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA]
Well, no. But, uh...

00:17:49.152 --> 00:17:51.029 position:50% align:center
There are a few other
seats on your council

00:17:51.112 --> 00:17:54.991 position:50% align:center
that need to be filled, so...
we were just wondering, um...

00:17:55.075 --> 00:17:56.201 position:50% align:center
As you know, both of us have

00:17:56.284 --> 00:17:58.953 position:50% align:center
severely dysfunctional
personalities.

00:17:59.037 --> 00:18:01.206 position:50% align:center
We're worried you won't
pick us again. That's all.

00:18:01.289 --> 00:18:02.707 position:50% align:center
What he said!

00:18:02.791 --> 00:18:04.751 position:50% align:center
[MIYUKI] I think my secretary
and treasurer should have

00:18:04.834 --> 00:18:08.213 position:50% align:center
a bit more composure,
wouldn't you agree?

00:18:08.296 --> 00:18:11.633 position:50% align:center
Our first job as the
new Student Council

00:18:11.716 --> 00:18:14.469 position:50% align:center
will be cleaning up the
gym, so let's hop to it.

00:18:14.552 --> 00:18:16.888 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA chuckles]

00:18:16.971 --> 00:18:18.181 position:50% align:center
[CHIKA, YU]
Right!

00:18:25.021 --> 00:18:28.358 position:50% align:center
Why hasn't the president
come to check on me yet?

00:18:30.360 --> 00:18:31.528 position:50% align:center
When he heard that I fainted,

00:18:31.611 --> 00:18:32.862 position:50% align:center
shouldn't he have
dropped everything

00:18:32.946 --> 00:18:34.614 position:50% align:center
and come running
to take care of me?!

00:18:34.698 --> 00:18:35.865 position:50% align:center
He just won an election

00:18:35.949 --> 00:18:37.575 position:50% align:center
and has the "privilege"
of cleaning up after,

00:18:37.659 --> 00:18:39.911 position:50% align:center
so he'll probably come
when he's done.

00:18:39.994 --> 00:18:41.413 position:50% align:center
Oh my gosh.

00:18:41.496 --> 00:18:44.666 position:50% align:center
What if he doesn't want me
to be on his council anymore?

00:18:44.749 --> 00:18:46.418 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA] It's astonishing
how much control

00:18:46.501 --> 00:18:48.378 position:50% align:center
your mind has over your body.

00:18:48.461 --> 00:18:50.672 position:50% align:center
Are you actually
concerned about that?

00:18:50.755 --> 00:18:53.425 position:50% align:center
You know full well what
my personality is like.

00:18:53.508 --> 00:18:55.719 position:50% align:center
What if the president discovered
the shady things I did

00:18:55.802 --> 00:18:59.014 position:50% align:center
to make the other candidate
drop out of the election?

00:18:59.097 --> 00:19:03.393 position:50% align:center
Or that I pestered a handful
of clubs into voting for him?

00:19:03.476 --> 00:19:04.853 position:50% align:center
Oh, no!

00:19:04.936 --> 00:19:06.271 position:50% align:center
What if he knows the members
of the election committee

00:19:06.354 --> 00:19:07.731 position:50% align:center
are my puppets?

00:19:07.814 --> 00:19:09.607 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA] Jeez, you really
went all out, didn't you?

00:19:09.691 --> 00:19:11.776 position:50% align:center
I mean, he only ran
because I asked him to,

00:19:11.860 --> 00:19:13.653 position:50% align:center
so of course I did!

00:19:13.737 --> 00:19:15.572 position:50% align:center
I promised myself I'd
do everything I could

00:19:15.655 --> 00:19:17.323 position:50% align:center
to get him re-elected.

00:19:17.407 --> 00:19:20.535 position:50% align:center
Wasn't that a logical decision?

00:19:20.618 --> 00:19:22.287 position:50% align:center
Well, you're a
paranoid mess now,

00:19:22.370 --> 00:19:25.874 position:50% align:center
so I don't think the juice was
worth the squeeze in this case.

00:19:25.957 --> 00:19:28.877 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA] I'm a horrible girl
who relied on foul play to win.

00:19:28.960 --> 00:19:30.503 position:50% align:center
If he doesn't want me
for Student Council,

00:19:30.587 --> 00:19:32.422 position:50% align:center
I can't say I blame him.

00:19:32.505 --> 00:19:35.508 position:50% align:center
Except I have every right to
blame him if he does that to me!

00:19:35.592 --> 00:19:36.926 position:50% align:center
Did you see what he
did with those votes

00:19:37.010 --> 00:19:38.678 position:50% align:center
we worked so hard
to scrounge up?

00:19:38.762 --> 00:19:40.096 position:50% align:center
Did you?!

00:19:40.180 --> 00:19:41.556 position:50% align:center
He just chucked 'em out the
first open window he saw

00:19:41.639 --> 00:19:43.641 position:50% align:center
without so much as
a second thought!

00:19:43.725 --> 00:19:45.143 position:50% align:center
[yells]

00:19:45.226 --> 00:19:46.770 position:50% align:center
He's like a typical
good-for-nothing husband

00:19:46.853 --> 00:19:48.605 position:50% align:center
whose wife works a
part-time job every night,

00:19:48.688 --> 00:19:49.981 position:50% align:center
but then he takes her
money and uses it

00:19:50.065 --> 00:19:53.276 position:50% align:center
for gambling, sex
workers, and booze!

00:19:53.360 --> 00:19:55.236 position:50% align:center
[KAGUYA breathing heavily]

00:19:55.320 --> 00:19:56.863 position:50% align:center
It'll be fine.

00:19:56.946 --> 00:19:58.573 position:50% align:center
He asked you to write
his campaign speech.

00:19:58.656 --> 00:20:00.533 position:50% align:center
He wouldn't have done that if he
didn't want you on his council.

00:20:00.617 --> 00:20:02.160 position:50% align:center
I'm the kind of woman
that gets used up

00:20:02.243 --> 00:20:03.620 position:50% align:center
and thrown out like
a piece of trash

00:20:03.703 --> 00:20:04.913 position:50% align:center
once I've served my purpose!

00:20:04.996 --> 00:20:07.540 position:50% align:center
[HAYASAKA] Anxious one
second, angry the next.

00:20:07.624 --> 00:20:08.708 position:50% align:center
You're hopeless.

00:20:08.792 --> 00:20:11.002 position:50% align:center
I actually fooled
myself into thinking

00:20:11.086 --> 00:20:12.545 position:50% align:center
the president liked me.

00:20:12.629 --> 00:20:16.383 position:50% align:center
I thought he was nice to me
because I was special.

00:20:16.466 --> 00:20:19.803 position:50% align:center
But I was wrong.
He's nice to everybody.

